# Security headers, applied to every response. connect-src is the allowlist of
# every host Aura may contact — the Govee cloud APIs (which set CORS headers,
# so the browser calls them directly) plus aura-server, the one small Worker
# behind the feedback box (never lights, keys, or scenes). Adding a host here
# is a security decision, not a config tweak.
#
# Permissions-Policy grants camera/microphone/geolocation to this origin
# (`self`) — identify/rename uses none of them, but QR setup-transfer (camera),
# ambient "listen for the room" (microphone), and sunrise/sunset automations
# (geolocation) all do. Granting here only makes the browser API reachable;
# every one of those still only ever starts from an explicit tap, per Aura's
# sensor-consent rule — this header must never be the thing that decides that,
# only the thing that stops it from being silently unreachable regardless.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://openapi.api.govee.com https://developer-api.govee.com https://aura-server.jdd994.workers.dev; manifest-src 'self'; worker-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=(self), geolocation=(self), interest-cohort=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
